MEMC Falls in Premarket Trading After Breaking Suntech Contract

-- B y   T o d d   W h i t e   a n d   C h r i s t o p h e r   M a r t i n
-- 
2011-07-01T12:23:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-01/memc-falls-in-premarket-trading-after-breaking-suntech-contract.html
MEMC Electronic Materials Inc. (WFR) , the
second-largest U.S. manufacturer of polysilicon, fell 1.6
percent to $8.39 in premarket trading on the Nasdaq stock market
after saying it ended a 10-year wafer supply contract with
Suntech Power Holdings Co.  China ’s Suntech, the world’s largest
producer of silicon solar panels, agreed to pay MEMC $67 million
and relinquish a $53 million deposit to cancel the contract,
according to a statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Todd White at 
 twhite2@bloomberg.net  